<!-- Status Logs -->
<div id="status_logs">
	<h1><tmpl_var _("webui", "status_logs_menu_text")></h1>
	<h2>Overview</h2>
	<p>
		The Log information is useful for troubleshooting, but is not required for normal operation.
	</p>
	
	<h2>Settings</h2>
	<h3><tmpl_var _("webui", "status_logs_enable_logs_label")></h3>
	<p>Turn on the logs as needed.</p>
	<h3><tmpl_var _("webui", "status_logs_delete_sys_logs_label")></h3>
	<p>This setting determines for how long the system log data is retained. 
	Select the desired option.</p>
	<p>Note that if the log is full, the oldest data is deleted, regardless of this setting.</p>
	
	<h2>Log Data</h2>
	<h3><tmpl_var _("webui", "status_logs_mobile_network_log_href")></h3>
	<p>This log contains data regarding connections to the mobile network.
	</p>
	<h3><tmpl_var _("webui", "status_logs_system_log_href")></h3>
	<p>This log records events&mdash;other than mobile data connections&mdash;which occurred on this device.
	</p>
	
	<h2>Buttons</h2>
	
	<h3><tmpl_var _("webui", "status_logs_refresh_btn")></h3>
	<p>Use this to update the log data which is displayed.</p>
	<h3><tmpl_var _("webui", "status_logs_download_btn")></h3>
	<p>Use this button if you wish to download log data to your computer or connected device.</p>
	<h3><tmpl_var _("webui", "status_logs_clear_log_btn")></h3>
	<p>Clicking this button will delete all existing log data. This makes new data easier to read.</p>
</div>
<!-- end Status Logs -->
